es-internautes-senflamment_a_23326933%2F\" target=\"_blank\"></a></li><li class=\"bN linkedin share-bar__item\" data-beacon=\'{\"p\":{\"lnid\":\"linkedin\",\"mpid\":11}}\'><a class=\"share-bar__item-link icon-Social_Linkedin\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.fr%2F2018%2F01%2F08%2Fsur-internet-h-and-m-fait-porter-un-sweat-a-message-a-un-enfant-noir-et-les-internautes-senflamment_a_23326933%2F\" target=\"_blank\"></a></li><li class=\"bN viadeo share-bar__item\" data-beacon=\'{\"p\":{\"lnid\":\"viadeo\",\"mpid\":12}}\'><a class=\"share-bar__item-link \" href=\"https://partners.viadeo.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.fr%2F2018%2F01%2F08%2Fsur-internet-h-and-m-fait-porter-un-sweat-a-message-a-un-enfant-noir-et-les-internautes-senflamment_a_23326933%2F\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"viadeo-icon\" src=\"http://www.blogsmithmedia.com/www.huffingtonpost.fr/assets-h38044f9f363644e9d36cb26664dffab0/images/icons/icon-viadeo.png?h=a78ad2c7a589a8709878dd08e86af70e\"></a></li></ul></script>\n\n        <div class=\"share-bar__social-counts\" >\n            <span class=\"share-bar__social-counts__number\"></span>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n            <div class=\"author-byline\">\n            <ul class=\"author-list\">\n                                                            <li class=\"author-card\">\n                            <div class=\"author-card__headshot\" style=\"background-image: url(http://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?thumbnail=40%2C40&image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.blogcdn.com%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.fr%2Fmedia%2F2017%2F12%2F1182497411789912987944372143993425427793073n-1.jpg&client=cbc79c14efcebee57402&signature=a6eaec578fda5893750f4753d1e09cb22603060c);\"></div>\n                            <div class=\"author-card__details\">\n                                <span class=\"author-card__details-container\">\n                                    <a class=\"author-card__details__name\" data-beacon=\'{\"p\":{\"lnid\":\"author\"}}\' href=\"/author/emeline-bertel\">\n                                        <span class=\"author-card__details__name\">\n                                        Emeline Bertel\n                                        </span>\n                                    </a>\n                                    <span class=\"author-card__social-container desktop-only\">\n                                                                                                                            <a class=\"author-card__social author-card__social--twitter icon-Social_Twitter\" data-beacon=\'{\"p\":{\"lnid\":\"author_twitter\"}}\' href=\"https://twitter.com/HeyMeline_Bnst\" target=\"_blank\"></a>\n                                                                                                                    </span>\n                                                                    </span>\n                                <span class=\"author-card__microbio desktop-only\">\n                                    Journaliste culture&nbsp;\n                                </span>\n                            </div>\n                        </li>\n                                                </ul>\n        </div>\n    </header>\n\n                    \n    </div>\n    \n                                                    \n                <div class=\"page__content\">\n                        \n    \n    <div class=\"page__content__row row--no-border\">\n                    <div class=\"col col--body-center\">\n                <div class=\"entry__below-entry \">\n                                            <article class=\"entry__content \">\n    \n        \n        \n    \n        \n            \n                                        \n            <div class=\"top-media\" data-beacon=\'{\"p\":{\"mnid\":\"top_media\"}}\'>\n                <div class=\"top-media--image image\">\n                    <img class=\"image__src\" src=\"https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims3/GLOB/crop/508x254+0+13/resize/630x315!/format/jpg/quality/85/http%3A%2F%2Fo.aolcdn.com%2Fhss%2Fstorage%2Fmidas%2F56721237d464c24e15fe1b37a71776ff%2F206008052%2Fh%2526m.JPG\">\n                    <div class=\"image__credit\">\n                        @CharlesMBlow/Twitter\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"image__caption\">\n                        Sur Internet, H&amp;M fait porter un sweat à message à un enfant noir et les internautes s&#039;enflamment\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n\n            \n    <div class=\"entry__body post-contents\" data-part=\"contents\">\n\n            <!-- ads_sharebox_260x60 -->\n    <div id=\"sharebox_260x60\" class=\n         \"advertisement sharebox_260x60\"  \"ad_spot desktop-only\">\n        \n    </div>\n\n                                                                \n        \n                    <p>POL&Eacute;MIQUE - &Eacute;norme fashion faux-pas pour <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/news/h-m/\" target=\"_blank\">H&amp;M</a>: pour le lancement de sa nouvelle collection pour les jeunes gar&ccedil;ons, la marque a mis en ligne, sur son site Internet au Royaume-Uni, une photo d\'un petit gar&ccedil;on noir portant un sweat &agrave; message.</p>\n                        \n                                                            <!-- entry_paragraph_1_ad -->\n    <div id=\"entry_paragraph_1\" class=\"entry-body--paragraph-ad\">\n    	<div class=\"ad_spot \"\n	        >\n	              	</div>\n    </div>\n                                                                \n\n<p>Probl&egrave;me, le texte dit: \"Coolest monkey in the jungle\" (\"le singe le plus cool de la jungle\"). Les internautes y ont vu une forme de <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/news/racisme/\" target=\"_blank\">racisme</a> ordinaire et ont largement critiqu&eacute; la marque pour ce manque de vigilance.</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                <!-- entry_paragraph_2_ad -->\n    <div id=\"entry_paragraph_2\" class=\"entry-body--paragraph-ad\">\n    	<div class=\"ad_spot \"\n	        >\n	              	</div>\n    </div>\n                                                                \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hm?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@hm</a>, have you lost your damned minds?!?!?! <a href=\"https://t.co/EYuCXLZtv3\">pic.twitter.com/EYuCXLZtv3</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n&mdash; Charles M. Blow (@CharlesMBlow) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CharlesMBlow/status/950208202154610689?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"H&amp;M, as-tu perdu la t&ecirc;te?!\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Had a hard time finding this, but that\'s because I was looking on the US site...it\'s on the UK version of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hm?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@hm</a>\'s website. <a href=\"https://t.co/CcEBWVUYaT\">https://t.co/CcEBWVUYaT</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/peQ5hc5wxI\">pic.twitter.com/peQ5hc5wxI</a></p>\n                                                    \n                                                            <!-- entry_paragraph_3_ad -->\n    <div id=\"entry_paragraph_3\" class=\"entry-body--paragraph-ad\">\n    	<div class=\"ad_spot \"\n	        >\n	              	</div>\n    </div>\n                                                                \n&mdash; Yashar Ali ? (@yashar) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/yashar/status/950250001342652417?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"J\'ai eu du mal &agrave; le trouver mais c\'est parce que je le cherchais sur le site am&eacute;ricain. Il n\'est disponible que sur le site britannique.\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<center>\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">More casual racism from H&amp;M. This is nothing new when it comes to these clothing companies like Abercrombie and Tommy Hilfilger who have a long history of using their products to convey racist messages. <a href=\"https://t.co/6XwimxngCS\">https://t.co/6XwimxngCS</a></p>\n                        \n                                                            <!-- entry_paragraph_4_ad -->\n    <div id=\"entry_paragraph_4\" class=\"entry-body--paragraph-ad\">\n    	<div class=\"ad_spot \"\n	        >\n	         <!-- TEMPLATE CODE -->\r\n<div id=\"dfp_inread\"  class=\"dfp clearfix ad-entry_paragraph_4\">\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    (function(){\r\n        var dfp_placement_slug = \'entry_paragraph_4\';\r\n        var dfp_slot_id = \'inread\';\r\n        var dfp_div_id = \"dfp_\" + dfp_slot_id;\r\n        var dfp_div_el = document.getElementById(dfp_div_id);\r\n\r\n        var dfp_prefix = dfpController.getDfpPrefix() || \"\";\r\n        if (dfp_prefix === \"\") dfpController.console.error(\"DFP prefix is empty\");\r\n        dfp_prefix = dfp_prefix + dfp_slot_id;\r\n\r\n        \r\n\r\n        var display_in_template = false;\r\n        \r\n\r\n        var out_of_page_slot = false;\r\n\r\n        dfpController.log(\"Slot:\" + dfp_placement_slug + \" -> \" + dfp_prefix + \"/\" + dfp_slot_id);\r\n\r\n        googletag.cmd.push(function(){\r\n            var dfp_slot = null;\r\n            if (out_of_page_slot) {\r\n                dfp_slot = googletag.defineOutOfPageSlot(dfp_prefix,\r\n                    dfp_div_id).setTargeting(\'pos\', dfp_slot_id).addService(googletag.pubads());\r\n            } else {\r\n                dfp_slot = googletag.defineSlot(dfp_prefix,\r\n                    dfpController.getSizeFromMapping(dfp_slot_id, dfp_placement_slug), dfp_div_id).setTargeting(\'pos\', dfp_slot_id).addService(googletag.pubads());\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            if ( display_in_template ) {\r\n                if ( !dfpController.hasCustomBidder() ) {\r\n                    dfpController.displaySlot(dfp_slot);\r\n                } else if ( dfpController.getCustomBidder().completed() ) {\r\n                    dfpController.displaySlot(dfp_slot, true);\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            dfpController.attachAdReloadEvent(dfp_div_el, dfp_slot);\r\n            return;\r\n        });\r\n        return;\r\n    })();\r\n    </script>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- TEMPLATE CODE ENDS -->     	</div>\n    </div>\n                                                                \n&mdash; Makkim (@Makkim77) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Makkim77/status/950242757439758336?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"Un peu plus de racisme ordinaire de la part d\'H&amp;M. Rien de surprenant vu que des marques comme Abercombie et Tommy Hilfiger ont un vrai passif avec des v&ecirc;tements portant des messages controvers&eacute;s et racistes.\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Uh oh, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hm?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@hm</a>. Can y\'all explain why a black boy was selected to model a hoodie that says, \"coolest monkey in the jungle\"? ?Someone didn\'t think this through. <a href=\"https://t.co/q0NwrboCnq\">https://t.co/q0NwrboCnq</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n&mdash; Christina Watkins (@CWatkinsTV) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CWatkinsTV/status/950200721512779777?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"Eh H&amp;M, tu peux nous expliquer pourquoi un gar&ccedil;on noir a &eacute;t&eacute; s&eacute;lectionn&eacute; comme mod&egrave;le pour porter un sweat qui dit \"Coolest monkey in the jungle\"? Quelqu\'un n\'est pas all&eacute; au bout de la r&eacute;flexion...\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hm?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@hm</a> this is disgusting &amp; irresponsible. You know the history of racist using the term \"monkey\" to demean people of African descent... and you put this on your website! ???? \"Coolest Monkey In the Jungle\" <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/SMH?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#SMH</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/IY877D2d8R\">pic.twitter.com/IY877D2d8R</a></p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n&mdash; Karamo Brown (@KaramoBrown) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KaramoBrown/status/950263920450715648?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"H&amp;M, ceci est d&eacute;go&ucirc;tant et irresponsable. Vous savez que l\'histoire du racisme utilise le terme \"singe\" pour d&eacute;signer les noirs africains... et vous osez mettre &ccedil;a sur votre site!\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Contact&eacute;e par <a href=\"http://www.europe1.fr/culture/handm-cree-la-polemique-avec-une-photo-a-connotation-raciste-3539984\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Europe 1</em></a>, la marque su&eacute;doise a assur&eacute; que la photo pol&eacute;mique \"a &eacute;t&eacute; retir&eacute;e de toutes les cha&icirc;nes H&amp;M\". H&amp;M a aussi pr&eacute;sent&eacute; ses excuses \"&agrave; quiconque ait pu &ecirc;tre offens&eacute;\".</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n\n<p>En effet, en r&eacute;action &agrave; ce d&eacute;but de pol&eacute;mique, H&amp;M a retir&eacute; la photo du jeune gar&ccedil;on qui n\'est, &agrave; ce jour, plus disponible sur le site du g&eacute;ant de l\'habillement. Seule la photo du sweat non-port&eacute; est toujours visible en ligne. Ce produit n\'est par ailleurs pas disponible sur le site fran&ccedil;ais de la marque. Les photos des autres mod&egrave;les (bleu et oranges) du v&ecirc;tement sont toujours en ligne sur la plateforme... mais ils sont eux port&eacute; par deux enfants blancs.</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/NerdAboutTown\" target=\"_blank\">Stephanie Yeboah</a>, une blogueuse mode grande taille londonienne, qui fut la premi&egrave;re personne &agrave; partager cette erreur de communication, a re&ccedil;u des dizaines de messages d\'insultes &agrave; la suite de sa publication sur Twitter.</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">What makes this worse, is that I now have a gaggle of white men in my mentions telling me that there is nothing wrong with this jumper.<br />\n<br />\nI am just...speechless. <a href=\"https://t.co/4AuX6FIm9E\">pic.twitter.com/4AuX6FIm9E</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n&mdash; Stephanie Yeboah (@NerdAboutTown) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/NerdAboutTown/status/950131585038286848?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">7 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"Le pire, c\'est que j\'ai maintenant tout un tas de r&eacute;actions d\'homme blancs qui se demandent qu\'est ce qui ne va pas avec ce sweat. Je suis juste... sans voix.\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Such nice messages to wake up to. <a href=\"https://t.co/hSS2iQ0WTA\">pic.twitter.com/hSS2iQ0WTA</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n&mdash; Stephanie Yeboah (@NerdAboutTown) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/NerdAboutTown/status/950273226122416128?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">8 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<p><em>\"Tant de messages adorables au r&eacute;veil\"</em></p>\n                        \n                                \n</center>\n</center>\n\n<center>\n<center><em><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></em></center>\n<em><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></em></center>\n\n<p></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<p>Face aux messages d\'incompr&eacute;hension et d\'insultes, la blogueuse mode a r&eacute;torqu&eacute; que \"Pour quelqu\'un qui a &eacute;t&eacute; trait&eacute; de singe &agrave; de nombreuses reprises par des personnes blanches (&agrave; la fois en face et en ligne), c\'est totalement inacceptable\" avant de poursuivre dans un autre tweet: \"De plus, si vous &ecirc;tes blancs, vous n\'avez absolument aucun droit pour dire aux personnes noires ce qu\'elles devraient ou non trouver raciste. Ce n\'est pas parce que vous n\'exp&eacute;rimentez pas vous-m&ecirc;mes le racisme que &ccedil;a n\'existe pas\"</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-conversation=\"none\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">As somebody who has been called a monkey many times by white people (both to my face and online), this is absolutely unacceptable.</p>\n                        \n                                \n&mdash; Stephanie Yeboah (@NerdAboutTown) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/NerdAboutTown/status/950133214961721344?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">7 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n\n<center>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-conversation=\"none\" data-lang=\"fr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Furthermore, if you\'re white, you have absolutely no room, right or scope to tell black people what we should and should not find racist.<br />\n<br />\nJust because YOU don\'t experience racism, it doesn\'t mean it doesn\'t exist.</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n&mdash; Stephanie Yeboah (@NerdAboutTown) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/NerdAboutTown/status/950133549289672705?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">7 janvier 2018</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n\n<p></p>\n                        \n                                \n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></center>\n\n<p>En 2014, <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2014/10/09/combinaison-hm-peshmerga-controverse_n_5957920.html?utm_hp_ref=fr-h-m\" target=\"_blank\">les internautes avaient &eacute;pingl&eacute; une combinaison</a> H&amp;M qui ressemblait un peu trop aux tuniques traditionnelles des femmes kurdes r&eacute;sistant aux attaques de l\'&Eacute;tat islamique &agrave; la fronti&egrave;re turco-syrienne. Par le biais de sa charg&eacute;e monde aux relations presses, Ida St&aring;hlnacke, la marque s\'&eacute;tait alors excus&eacute;e: \"Nous sommes sinc&egrave;rement d&eacute;sol&eacute;s si nous avons offens&eacute;s quelqu\'un avec ce v&ecirc;tement, ce n\'&eacute;tait en rien notre intention\", avait-elle d&eacute;clar&eacute; au <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2782418/H-M-apologises-Peshmerga-chic-jumpsuit-Clothing-chain-embarrassed-accused-modelling-15-khaki-outfit-uniform-worn-Kurdish-female-fighters-battling-ISIS.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Daily Mail</em></a>.</p>\n                        \n                                                                                                            \n\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Lire aussi :</strong></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<p>&bull; <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2016/09/16/hm-campagne-2016-celebre-femmes-au-quotidien_n_12044420.html?utm_hp_ref=fr-h-m\" target=\"_blank\">La campagne automne/hiver 2016 de H&amp;M c&eacute;l&egrave;bre (enfin) toutes les femmes</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<p>&bull; <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2016/06/16/hm-tailles-petites-critique-_n_10504150.html?utm_hp_ref=fr-h-m\" target=\"_blank\">Elle trouve les tailles d\'H&amp;M trop petites, et elle le fait savoir sur Facebook</a></p>\n                        \n                                \n\n<p>&bull; <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2015/12/01/pub-hm-emmaus-close-the-loop-recyclage-ecologie-video_n_8686250.html?utm_hp_ref=fr-h-m\" target=\"_blank\">Emma&uuml;s a recycl&eacute; une pub H&amp;M pour faire passer un message</a></p>\n                        \n                                     